				I think the only thing I find shocking about this whole situation is your article. Since the begining of this game Verant has continualy printed on it's boxes, CD's, and EULA that the system requirements can change without notice. Computers double in power almost every eighteen months. It stands to reason that older OS's will not be supported as a game grows. It's hard enough to code for somehting that supports a broad range of OS/Video Card/Soundcard/Internet Connection/ and a hundred other variables. I really feel that you haven't considered the one true constant in this whole sitation. This game was done to make the creator money. As long as Everquest continues to be profitable- then it will continue to exsist. The company can't make everyone happy at the same time. They did polls constantly over the months prior to Luclin release to see what systems people were running. Obviously the majority of the players were using close to, or above the new minium specs for the expansion. Not everything a corporation does is a conspiricy to get you. A lot of it is based on demographic data provided by YOU. For all the aggrivation you are letting yourself have with this little &quot;crusade&quot; of yours. Why don't you just buy Win 98? Think of it as computer Darwinism. Evolve or die. Rules and regulations are there for a reason. We may not agree totally with the letter of them, but we should respect the ideas they represent. By virtue of instaling the game Everquest and logging on you have agreed to abide by the rules of their game. If you can't do that, Uninstall the game and toss the CD in the trash. My personal opinion is that too many people try to hide behind legal action nowadays. &quot;I'll sue you for looking at me funny.&quot; Sounds funny, but its been done. If the courts imposed a fine or sentance on people who started frivilous lawsuits or feigned legal action, I doubt we would see to many articles like yours anymore. Computer Darwinism- evolve or die. If you can't handle it- go play pong. *tho I loved that game ;)*<BR>

